solutions.content:
# Intuition
The question wants us to implement a data structure that can efficiently return the minimum element in infinite set of integers, first thought comes to mind is minHeap as it will always contains minimum element at top and operation would take O(1) time.

- **Heap** will store the minimum of the elements that are addedBack via addBack() method
- minNum or say counter will keep track of continous non popped elements

---


# Approach
Look at dry run example below approach to understand code better.
### *addBack()*
1) If the number to be added(num) is less than minNum ie ```num < minNum```, then it means that num has not been popped yet.
2) Also we don't want to add duplicates, so if nums is already present in heap we don't add it.
3) else add to heap

### *popSmallest*()
1) If the heap is not empty ```!heap.isEmpty()``` then we return top element from heap and remove it.
2) Incase heap is empty then we increment minNum and return minNum-1
, minNum keeps the track of numbers we have taken out till now.

----
Example
*Operation* - popSmallest
result 1 : (heap empty --> increment minNum --> minNum = 2)

*Operation* - popSmallest
result 2 : (heap empty --> increment minNum --> minNum = 3)

*Operation* - addBack(2)
added to heap : minNum > num  (3>2 and !heap.contains(2))
add to heap --> heap contains 2 now

*Operation* - popSmallest
result 2 not 3 as we will return from heap which is not empty

*Operation* - popSmallest
result 3 (heap empty --> increment minNum --> = minNum 4)

*Operation* - addSmallest(5)
5 will not be added as minNum > num not satisfied 4>5 (this means num=5 is not popped yet)

---
***P.S*** This is a tricky question if you solve it considering infinite integers and not 1000 integer upperbound, If asked in interview interviewer won't except asnwer with 1000 intialisation of heap or hashset in the constructor.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(nlogn) : minHeapigy take logn each time, assuming n opertions happen at max nlogn will be complexity

- Space complexity:
O(n) in worst case

----
Hope it is easy to understand.
Let me know if there is something unclear and i can fix it.

Otherwise, please upvote if you like the solution, it would be encouraging


