2. When popSmallest() is called then, *look* at the beginning of the set(st.begin()), becuase it store values in *ascending order* and return this value then *erase* from the set.
3. When addBack() call is made, then simply insert *num* in the set because if *duplicate* is their then it do nothing otherwise it will *insert* into it.
