```
- currSmallest starts at 1
- If you pop, currSmallest is now 2, pop again, currSmallest 
 is now 3
- Now the series looks like this [3, 4, ....]
- You can add a number which is smallest than currSmallest
- Add this number to the set S
- So, if we add 2, now it looks like this... S = {2},
  currSmallest = 3
- Add back 1. S = {1, 2}, currSmallest = 3

- When you try popping, since set contains only numbers that are
  smaller than the currSmallest, we choose the smallest in
  the set.
- Smallest in the set is 1, we return this & remove it from the
  set S
- S = {2}, currSmallest = 3

- If you pop again... since S is not empty, after popping it
  will look like this... S = {}, currSmallest = 3
- Now if you try popping again, since set S is empty, we are
  sure no element is smaller that the currSmallest. Hence we
  return currSmallest and increment by 1. currSmallest is now 4
- And so on...
```

